      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CLYBURN (8) finished midfield on debut (22.92) then better for the experience broke through last time to score a nose maiden win (23.02) at Richmond. Can make it back-to-back wins. CAWBOURNE ZARA (2) was resuming when finishing fourth at this track in a Grade 5 (20.42). Solid record here winning two races. Smart beginner who should take advantage of the low draw. Should play a prominent role. STAY TIPSY (1) settled close to the lead but checked in the run and turned spotting a start, missing the frame when fifth (20.71) at this track over 350m in a Grade 5. With a good start should be able to take advantage of the rails draw. Bold showing expected on best. VALEDICTORIAN (6) was below best last time at Wentworth Park (30.30) in a NG, finishing a 9 length seventh. Has three wins already from this draw.",
